<Link id="l00009" /><CodeLine lineNumber="9"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This pass lowers LLVM IR exception handling into something closer to what the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00010" /><CodeLine lineNumber="10"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// backend wants for functions using a personality function from a runtime</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00011" /><CodeLine lineNumber="11"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// provided by MSVC. Functions with other personality functions are left alone</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00012" /><CodeLine lineNumber="12"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// and may be prepared by other passes. In particular, all supported MSVC</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00013" /><CodeLine lineNumber="13"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// personality functions require cleanup code to be outlined, and the C++</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00014" /><CodeLine lineNumber="14"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// personality requires catch handler code to be outlined.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00015" /><CodeLine lineNumber="15"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00289" /><CodeLine lineNumber="289"><span class="doxyHighlight">&#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00290" /><CodeLine lineNumber="290"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00291" /><CodeLine lineNumber="291"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The central theory of this routine is based on the following:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00292" /><CodeLine lineNumber="292"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   A &#95;try scope is always a SEME (Single Entry Multiple Exits) region</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00293" /><CodeLine lineNumber="293"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     as jumping into a &#95;try is not allowed</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00294" /><CodeLine lineNumber="294"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   The single entry must start with a seh&#95;try&#95;begin() invoke with a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00295" /><CodeLine lineNumber="295"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     correct State number that is the initial state of the SEME.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00296" /><CodeLine lineNumber="296"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   Through control-flow, state number is propagated into all blocks.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00297" /><CodeLine lineNumber="297"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   Side exits marked by seh&#95;try&#95;end() will unwind to parent state via</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00298" /><CodeLine lineNumber="298"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     existing SEHUnwindMap&#91;&#93;.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00299" /><CodeLine lineNumber="299"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   Side exits can ONLY jump into parent scopes (lower state number).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00300" /><CodeLine lineNumber="300"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   Thus, when a block succeeds various states from its predecessors,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00301" /><CodeLine lineNumber="301"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     the lowest State trumphs others.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00302" /><CodeLine lineNumber="302"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   If some exits flow to unreachable, propagation on those paths terminate,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00303" /><CodeLine lineNumber="303"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     not affecting remaining blocks.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00654" /><CodeLine lineNumber="654"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00655" /><CodeLine lineNumber="655"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This numbering assigns one state number to each catchpad and cleanuppad.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00656" /><CodeLine lineNumber="656"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// It also computes two tree-like relations over states:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00657" /><CodeLine lineNumber="657"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 1) Each state has a &quot;HandlerParentState&quot;, which is the state of the next</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00658" /><CodeLine lineNumber="658"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    outer handler enclosing this state&#39;s handler (same as nearest ancestor</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00659" /><CodeLine lineNumber="659"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    per the ParentPad linkage on EH pads, but skipping over catchswitches).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00660" /><CodeLine lineNumber="660"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 2) Each state has a &quot;TryParentState&quot;, which:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00661" /><CodeLine lineNumber="661"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    a) for a catchpad that&#39;s not the last handler on its catchswitch, is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00662" /><CodeLine lineNumber="662"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       the state of the next catchpad on that catchswitch</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00663" /><CodeLine lineNumber="663"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    b) for all other pads, is the state of the pad whose try region is the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00664" /><CodeLine lineNumber="664"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       next outer try region enclosing this state&#39;s try region.  The &quot;try</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00665" /><CodeLine lineNumber="665"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       regions are not present as such in the IR, but will be inferred</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00666" /><CodeLine lineNumber="666"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       based on the placement of invokes and pads which reach each other</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00667" /><CodeLine lineNumber="667"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       by exceptional exits</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00668" /><CodeLine lineNumber="668"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Catchswitches do not get their own states, but each gets mapped to the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00669" /><CodeLine lineNumber="669"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// state of its first catchpad.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00670" /><CodeLine lineNumber="670"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00671" /><CodeLine lineNumber="671"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Step one: walk down from outermost to innermost funclets, assigning each</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00672" /><CodeLine lineNumber="672"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// catchpad and cleanuppad a state number.  Add an entry to the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00673" /><CodeLine lineNumber="673"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// ClrEHUnwindMap for each state, recording its HandlerParentState and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00674" /><CodeLine lineNumber="674"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// handler attributes.  Record the TryParentState as well for each catchpad</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00675" /><CodeLine lineNumber="675"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// that&#39;s not the last on its catchswitch, but initialize all other entries&#39;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00676" /><CodeLine lineNumber="676"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// TryParentStates to a sentinel -1 value that the next pass will update.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00677" /><CodeLine lineNumber="677"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00678" /><CodeLine lineNumber="678"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Seed a worklist with pads that have no parent.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00679" /><CodeLine lineNumber="679"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvector">SmallVector&lt;std::pair&lt;const Instruction &#42;, int&gt;</a>, 8&gt; Worklist;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00680" /><CodeLine lineNumber="680"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicblock">BasicBlock</a> &amp;BB : &#42;Fn) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00681" /><CodeLine lineNumber="681"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/instruction">Instruction</a> &#42;FirstNonPHI = &amp;&#42;BB.getFirstNonPHIIt();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00682" /><CodeLine lineNumber="682"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/value">Value</a> &#42;ParentPad;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00683" /><CodeLine lineNumber="683"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &#42;CPI = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a22eeee01734061ac1b31ccd994c49eef">dyn&#95;cast&lt;CleanupPadInst&gt;</a>(FirstNonPHI))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00684" /><CodeLine lineNumber="684"><span class="doxyHighlight">      ParentPad = CPI-&gt;getParentPad();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00685" /><CodeLine lineNumber="685"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">else</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (</span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &#42;CSI = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a22eeee01734061ac1b31ccd994c49eef">dyn&#95;cast&lt;CatchSwitchInst&gt;</a>(FirstNonPHI))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00686" /><CodeLine lineNumber="686"><span class="doxyHighlight">      ParentPad = CSI-&gt;getParentPad();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00687" /><CodeLine lineNumber="687"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">else</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00688" /><CodeLine lineNumber="688"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">continue</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00689" /><CodeLine lineNumber="689"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#a92ca992e52dddc420f4b069cae06dfbe">isa&lt;ConstantTokenNone&gt;</a>(ParentPad))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00690" /><CodeLine lineNumber="690"><span class="doxyHighlight">      Worklist.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl/#a396fcfee6914c76974b73c3d203da6a5">emplace&#95;back</a>(FirstNonPHI, -1);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00691" /><CodeLine lineNumber="691"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00692" /><CodeLine lineNumber="692"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00693" /><CodeLine lineNumber="693"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Use the worklist to visit all pads, from outer to inner.  Record</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00694" /><CodeLine lineNumber="694"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// HandlerParentState for all pads.  Record TryParentState only for catchpads</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00695" /><CodeLine lineNumber="695"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// that aren&#39;t the last on their catchswitch (setting all other entries&#39;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00696" /><CodeLine lineNumber="696"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// TryParentStates to an initial value of -1).  This loop is also responsible</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00697" /><CodeLine lineNumber="697"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// for setting the EHPadStateMap entry for all catchpads, cleanuppads, and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00698" /><CodeLine lineNumber="698"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// catchswitches.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00699" /><CodeLine lineNumber="699"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">while</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (!Worklist.<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectortemplatecommon/#ad9a3c7bc26b130377bbafc170b5f88a2">empty</a>()) &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01344" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1344"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicblock">BasicBlock</a> &#42;PHIBlock = UsingInst-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicblock/#a1b4bf7c97cdc8159fd73d48063f0b250">getParent</a>();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01345" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1345"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicblock">BasicBlock</a> &#42;NewBlock = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#adf83581f514774264d616eef5706cf6e">SplitEdge</a>(IncomingBlock, PHIBlock);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01346" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1346"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// SplitEdge gives us:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01347" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1347"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   IncomingBlock:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01348" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1348"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     ...</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01349" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1349"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     br label %NewBlock</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01350" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1350"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   NewBlock:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01351" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1351"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     catchret label %PHIBlock</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01352" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1352"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// But we need:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01353" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1353"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   IncomingBlock:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01354" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1354"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     ...</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01355" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1355"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     catchret label %NewBlock</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01356" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1356"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   NewBlock:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01357" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1357"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//     br label %PHIBlock</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01358" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1358"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// So move the terminators to each others&#39; blocks and swap their</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01359" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1359"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// successors.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01360" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1360"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/branchinst">BranchInst</a> &#42;Goto = <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#ac4fc845f5ed92de63cd4474f128f5fc5">cast&lt;BranchInst&gt;</a>(IncomingBlock-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicblock/#aef9e9fcf4c5dfce90276ca16d91b8e46">getTerminator</a>());</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01361" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1361"><span class="doxyHighlight">      Goto-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/instruction/#a0fd53f63d349dc8a7c5fc0cdd7a94c8d">removeFromParent</a>();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01362" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1362"><span class="doxyHighlight">      CatchRet-&gt;removeFromParent();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01363" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1363"><span class="doxyHighlight">      CatchRet-&gt;insertInto(IncomingBlock, IncomingBlock-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicblock/#a0b4e7bee9b8575cc7db73329f1a561bd">end</a>());</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01364" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1364"><span class="doxyHighlight">      Goto-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/instruction/#afcd9d2ea284c4d90541291ff9c47d332">insertInto</a>(NewBlock, NewBlock-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicblock/#a0b4e7bee9b8575cc7db73329f1a561bd">end</a>());</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01366" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1366"><span class="doxyHighlight">      CatchRet-&gt;setSuccessor(NewBlock);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01367" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1367"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Update the color mapping for the newly split edge.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01368" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1368"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Grab a reference to the ColorVector to be inserted before getting the</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l01370" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1370"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// element in BlockColors might cause the map to be reallocated.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01371" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1371"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#ac16c24df0637600996c9c6081da170a2">ColorVector</a> &amp;ColorsForNewBlock = BlockColors&#91;NewBlock&#93;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01372" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1372"><span class="doxyHighlight">      <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#ac16c24df0637600996c9c6081da170a2">ColorVector</a> &amp;ColorsForPHIBlock = BlockColors&#91;PHIBlock&#93;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01373" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1373"><span class="doxyHighlight">      ColorsForNewBlock = ColorsForPHIBlock;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01374" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1374"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">for</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/basicblock">BasicBlock</a> &#42;FuncletPad : ColorsForPHIBlock)</span></CodeLine>
